def: Opposition by which the quality opposed asquires strength;resistance or reaction roused by opposition or by the action of anopposite principle or quality.
The doctrine that all things are subject to fate, or that theytake place by inevitable necessity.

One of the attendants of a prince or noble, permanently chargedwith the performance of this office for his master. "I was the king'scupbearer." Neh. i. 11.
A castle and domain conferred on a nobleman for life. [Poland]Brande & C.
A division of boring Hymenoptera, including Tremex and alliedgenera. See Illust. of Horntail.
